00044       the function takes the matrix a, the result vector b, and the unkown

00048  *******************************************************************************

00057

00059 int
00060 correct_command_svd(double **a, double *b, double svdr, double svdt, double *x, int n_dim)
00061 {

00074 
00075   /* Copy a into u. */

00083

00086   my_svdcmp(u, N_SVD, N_SVD, w, v);

00088

00095   for (j = 1; j <= N_SVD; j++)

00129 /*!*****************************************************************************
00130  *******************************************************************************
00131 \note  check_svd
00132 \date  8/4/92
00133 
00134 \remarks 
00135 
00136       the matrices a, u, and v are reconstructed from the corrected matrix w.
00137       The squared errors denote how close the new matrices are to the
00138       original ones.
00139 
00140  *******************************************************************************
00141  Function Parameters: [in]=input,[out]=output
00142 
00143  \param[in]     a : matrix of linear equation a x = b
00144  \param[in]     u : matrix of nullspace columns
00145  \param[in]     w : vector with values of the diagonal matrix w
00146  \param[in]     v : matrix of columns of range
00147 
00148  ******************************************************************************/
00149 int
00150 check_svd(double **a, double **u, double *w, double **v)
00151 {
00152   double            **check_a, **check_u, **check_v;
00153   double              sum_a_errors, sum_u_errors, sum_v_errors;
00154   int                 i, j, k;
00155 
00156   check_a = my_matrix(1, N_SVD, 1, N_SVD);
00157   check_u = my_matrix(1, N_SVD, 1, N_SVD);
00158   check_v = my_matrix(1, N_SVD, 1, N_SVD);
00159 
00160   /* Check singular value decomposition. */
00161   sum_a_errors = 0.0;
00162   sum_u_errors = 0.0;
00163   sum_v_errors = 0.0;
00164   for (i = 1; i <= N_SVD; i++) {
00165     for (j = 1; j <= N_SVD; j++) {
00166       check_a[i][j] = 0.0;
00167       check_u[i][j] = 0.0;
00168       check_v[i][j] = 0.0;
00169       for (k = 1; k <= N_SVD; k++) {
00170         check_a[i][j] += u[i][k] * w[k] * v[j][k];      /* rebuilds matrix a */
00171         check_u[i][j] += u[k][i] * u[k][j];     /* since transpose equals
00172                                                  * inverse here this should
00173                                                  * become the Identity mat. */
00174         check_v[i][j] += v[k][i] * v[k][j];     /* the same as for u */
00175       }
00176       sum_a_errors += (check_a[i][j] - a[i][j]) * (check_a[i][j] - a[i][j]);
00177       /* printf( "%d %d %10.3g %10.3g %g\n", i, j, a[i][j], check_a[i][j],
00178        * check_a[i][j]-a[i][j] ); */
00179       if (i == j) {
00180         sum_u_errors += (check_u[i][j] - 1.0) * (check_u[i][j] - 1.0);
00181         sum_v_errors += (check_v[i][j] - 1.0) * (check_v[i][j] - 1.0);
00182       } else {
00183         sum_u_errors += check_u[i][j] * check_u[i][j];
00184         sum_v_errors += check_v[i][j] * check_v[i][j];
00185       }
00186     }
00187   }
00188 /*
00189   printf( "Check_svd:\n" );
00190   printf( "Sum of errors squared in reconstructing a: %g\n", sum_a_errors );
00191   printf( "Sum of errors squared in checking u: %g\n", sum_u_errors );
00192   printf( "Sum of errors squared in checking v: %g\n", sum_v_errors );
00193 */
00194 
00195   my_free_matrix(check_v, 1, N_SVD, 1, N_SVD);
00196   my_free_matrix(check_u, 1, N_SVD, 1, N_SVD);
00197   my_free_matrix(check_a, 1, N_SVD, 1, N_SVD);
00198 
00199   return TRUE;
00200 }
